    <note>Lin(1) Yi [1162] Nobody knows where his ancestors came from. At the end of the Tang, they fled the Huang(2) Chao [3409] rebellion and moved to Nanjian, Youqi xian. His father, Ji [3568], was the first jinshi in the family in 1046. He was also the first jinshi from Youqi xian. Yi was the only son of Ji's second wife, Xu(3) Shi, whose daughter was betrothed to Xu(3) Min [3379]. Wu(3) Ze [4026], a Nanjian, Jianpu resident, who earned the jinshi in 1079, was Ji's son-in-law through a daughter of his first wife. Zhang Kuo, WJ, 8.4a, 6a; Fujian TZ; XNYL, 149.3a; Huang Shang, WJ, 33.1a. CBD, 2, 1333.</note>
